HEADWORD: Satan
<hw>Sa"tan</hw> <pr>(s⟦amac⟧"t⟦ait⟧n, s⟦acr⟧t"⟦ait⟧n <mark>obs</mark>
)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb. <ets>s⟦amac⟧t⟦amac⟧n</ets> an
adversary, fr. <ets>s⟦amac⟧tan</ets> to be adverse, to persecute: cf.
Gr. <grk>Sata^n</grk>, <grk>Satana^s</grk>, L. <ets>Satan</ets>,
<ets>Satanas</ets>.]</ety> <def>The grand adversary of man; the Devil,
or Prince of darkness; the chief of the fallen angels; the
archfiend.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

